apiDescription: The prefetch intrinsic is a hint to the code generator to insert a prefetch instruction if supported; otherwise, it is a noop. Prefetches have no effect on the behavior of the program but can change its performance characteristics.
The locality argument must be a constant integer and is a temporal locality specifier ranging from (0) - no locality, to (3) - extremely local keep in cache
